summary: Secrets from the set of 'Killing Eve' season 2
title: Secrets from the set of 'Killing Eve' season 2
excerpt: “Hello! Lovely to meet you,” the doll-faced blonde says brightly, palm outstretched. And she does seem lovely — like a…
description:
This is filled with spoilers. Interesting non-spoilerish tidbits:

  • “The thing about the show is that it walks such a delicate line between hilarious and beautiful and crazy, but also kind of honest,” says head writer Emerald Fennell, who has taken over the season 2 reins from her good friend Phoebe Waller-Bridge.*   
  • (Don’t look to novelist Luke Jennings’ source material for future plot points, though; while he is still “very much a part of the process and gives his full blessing,” Day explains, the series is now officially off book.)
  • [Sean Delaney who plays Kenny] confesses that he wasn’t originally meant to stick around so long — let alone be Carolyn’s offspring. One day, he recalls, “I guess we’d been making the same gestures, and Sandra said, ‘You’re like mother and son!’ Phoebe took her [headphones] off and went, ‘What? Hold that thought.‘”**

* It cracks me up so much that the friendship between PWB and Emerald Fennell is always emphasized, as if the friendship will attest to a similarity of creative perspective when that’s not necessarily true? It might attest to trust between PWB and Fennell but from a stand point of how the show will progress and/or be made under Fennell’s direction, the fact that they are friends doesn’t mean much. In fact…

** Holy moly, the other day I was discussing PWB being receptive to input, like Sandra Oh’s huge input into the finale’s climax, but that the familial connection between the Martens was an off-hand comment on set that turned into one of the moments that literally made me gasp aloud when it was revealed in an episode is blowing my mind. (What a good reveal!) And I wonder how many creatives would be so open to snatching an idea out of the air on a whim like that. That may be a quality of PWB, to seize on an idea wherever it comes from and run with it.

summary:
Just to be clear.
To reply to some of the posts I read (playfully! Nothing serious here)...
I’m straight if that still means...
body:
Just to be clear.

To reply to some of the posts I read (playfully! Nothing serious here)…

I’m straight if that still means something (or better, quoting, I just fall in love with whoever I fall in love) I don’t give a fuck about the last season of Game of Thrones and I’m excited, deadly excited about Killing Eve 2 so much that, having to take two intercontinental flights at the end of March and on the 4th of April, I’m afraid to die before being able to watch the whole series.
